  "prompt": "You are taking a TIER 2 technical evaluation for STANDARD models.\n\nSolve 5 JavaScript exercises inspired by a middle school curriculum (4ème).\n\nReturn your answers in Markdown using headers for the exercise IDs and code blocks for the JavaScript functions.\n\n[EXERCISE Math]\nWrite a JavaScript function \"pythagore(coteA, coteB)\" that computes the hypotenuse using the Pythagorean theorem (sqrt(A^2 + B^2)).\n\n[EXERCISE Francais]\nWrite a JavaScript function \"conjuguerJe(verbe)\" that takes a regular \"-er\" verb (like \"chanter\") and returns it conjugated with \"je \" in present tense (e.g. \"je chante\"). Just replace \"er\" with \"e\".\n\n[EXERCISE Chimie]\nWrite a JavaScript function \"melanger(couleur1, couleur2)\" that returns \"vert\" if the colors are \"bleu\" and \"jaune\" (in any order), and \"marron\" otherwise.\n\n[EXERCISE Geo]\nWrite a JavaScript function \"compterPays(tableau)\" that returns the length of the array.\n\n[EXERCISE React]\nWrite a JavaScript function \"SimpleComponent(props)\" that simulates a React component by returning a string like \"<div>{titre}</div>\" where {titre} is replaced by props.titre.\n\nExpected Markdown format:\n### tache_X\n```javascript\nfunction solution() { ... }\n```",
  "tasks": [
